## 1. Equilibrium Propagation: Bridging the Gap Between Energy-Based Models and Backpropagation
**arxiv_id:** 1602.05179 | **upvotes:** 1
https://huggingface.co/papers/1602.05179
**Keywords:** energy-based models, Equilibrium Propagation, Backpropagation, Contrastive Hebbian Learning, Contrastive Divergence
**Summary:** Equilibrium Propagation is a learning framework for energy-based models that computes gradients through a single type of neural computation performed in both prediction and training phases, enabling error propagation without explicit backward passes.

## 2. Better Models, Faster Training: Sigmoid Attention for single-cell Foundation Models
**arxiv_id:** 2604.27124 | **upvotes:** 11
https://huggingface.co/papers/2604.27124
**Keywords:** sigmoid attention, softmax attention, attention mechanisms, cell-type separation, cell-type cohesion
**Summary:** Sigmoid attention improves biological foundation model training by providing better representations, faster convergence, and enhanced stability compared to softmax attention through bounded derivatives and diagonal Jacobian structure.

## 3. A Theoretical Framework for Inference Learning
**arxiv_id:** 2206.00164 | **upvotes:** 0
https://huggingface.co/papers/2206.00164
**Keywords:** backpropagation, inference learning algorithm, implicit stochastic gradient descent, explicit stochastic gradient descent, neurobiological models
**GitHub:** https://github.com/nalonso2/iltheory (1 stars)
**Summary:** IL, a biologically plausible alternative to backpropagation, is theoretically linked to implicit stochastic gradient descent, improving its stability and convergence.

## 4. Curl Descent: Non-Gradient Learning Dynamics with Sign-Diverse Plasticity
**arxiv_id:** 2510.02765 | **upvotes:** 1
https://huggingface.co/papers/2510.02765
**Keywords:** gradient-based algorithms, synaptic plasticity, gradient descent, inhibitory-excitatory connectivity, Hebbian plasticity
